# Investigation Report: Free Data Sources for Automated Phone/Laptop/Car/Accessories Comparison Website

**Objective**: Identify all viable free (open-source, free APIs, free tiers) data sources for fully automated fetching of product specifications, images, prices, and AI-generated reviews across phones, laptops, cars, and accessories -- with zero manual data entry and zero paid services.

---

## 1. FREE PHONE SPECIFICATION SOURCES

### 1.1 Self-Hosted GSMArena Scrapers (BEST FREE OPTION)

| Source | URL | What It Offers | Free Limits | API Key |
|--------|-----|---------------|-------------|---------|
| **RevengerNick/mobile-specs-api** | https://github.com/RevengerNick/mobile-specs-api | Full GSMArena scrape via REST API. Endpoints: `/brands`, `/brands/:slug`, `/:phone_slug`, `/latest`, `/top-by-interest`, `/top-by-fans`, `/search`. Built with Fastify + TypeScript. | Unlimited (self-hosted) | None required |
| **azharimm/phone-specs-api** | https://github.com/azharimm/phone-specs-api | Hosted public API at `api-mobilespecs.azharimm.dev`. Same GSMArena data with v2 endpoints. Brands, phones, search, latest, top-by-interest/fans. | Free hosted version available; can also self-host | None required |
| **raffyxyz/api-gsm-arena** | https://github.com/raffyxyz/api-gsm-arena | Unofficial GSM Arena API. Processor, camera, battery, etc. | Unlimited (self-hosted) | None required |
| **nordmarin/gsmarena-api** | https://github.com/nordmarin/gsmarena-api | GSMArena phone specification finder, reads from GSMArena, returns JSON. Early development. | Unlimited (self-hosted) | None required |

**Recommendation**: **RevengerNick/mobile-specs-api** is the strongest option. It is MIT-licensed, self-hostable, requires no API key, and provides comprehensive structured JSON from GSMArena's full database (13,000+ phones). Deploy it as a microservice and call it from your pipeline.

### 1.2 Hosted Phone Spec APIs with Free Tiers

| Source | URL | What It Offers | Free Tier | API Key |
|--------|-----|---------------|-----------|---------|
| **MobileAPI.dev** | https://mobileapi.dev/ | 31,563+ devices (phones, tablets, laptops, wearables). 12 spec categories, product images (base64), fuzzy search, autocomplete. | 50 requests/month, 5 req/min. No credit card. | Required (free signup) |
| **TechSpecs API** | https://developer.techspecs.io/ | 240,000+ products including 29k+ smartphones, 183k+ laptops, 2k+ tablets, 300+ smartwatches, 13k+ displays, 19k+ GPUs. Daily updates. Product images. Launch prices. | Free trial with limited calls. Unlimited plan is paid. Data is digitally watermarked -- caching/storing without authorization is forbidden. | Required |
| **FonoApi** | https://github.com/shakee93/fonoapi | 6,800+ mobile device descriptions. Open source. | Free | Required |

**Warning on TechSpecs**: Their ToS explicitly forbids caching or storing data without a commercial license. This makes it unsuitable for a static site that needs to persist data locally.

### 1.3 Other Phone Data Sources

| Source | URL | What It Offers | Free Tier | API Key |
|--------|-----|---------------|-----------|---------|
| **PhoneDB.net** | https://phonedb.net/ | 25,736+ device datasheets with 290+ parameters each. Covers smartphones, tablets, smartwatches, PDAs from 1989 to present. | NOT FREE. Paid licensing starting at 100+ EUR. Contact required. | N/A (paid license) |
| **DeviceSpecifications.com** | https://www.devicespecifications.com/ | Detailed phone specs with measurements, photos, graphs, comparison tables. | No public API. Would require scraping (ToS risk). | N/A |
| **Kimovil** | https://www.kimovil.com/ | Phone specs with real-time prices from multiple retailers. Good for price comparison data. | No official API. Community scraper exists on GitHub (`Matheus-Garbelini/kimovil_list_phones_by_processor`). Scraping only. | N/A |
| **Smartprix** (via Parse.bot) | https://parse.bot/ | Smartphones, tablets, laptops with specs, historical pricing, live deals. | Parse.bot marketplace -- pricing unclear | Via Parse.bot |

