## 2. FREE LAPTOP SPECIFICATION SOURCES

| Source | URL | What It Offers | Free Tier | API Key |
|--------|-----|---------------|-----------|---------|
| **TechSpecs API** | https://developer.techspecs.io/ | 183,000+ laptops with standardized specs. Daily updates. | Free trial only; caching forbidden by ToS | Required |
| **MobileAPI.dev** | https://mobileapi.dev/ | Includes laptops in their 31,563+ device database alongside phones/tablets/wearables. | 50 free requests/month | Required (free) |
| **NotebookCheck** | https://www.notebookcheck.net/ | Comprehensive laptop reviews, benchmarks, specs. Laptop search database. | No API. Would require custom scraping with BeautifulSoup/Scrapy. | N/A |
| **Kaggle Datasets** | https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/durgeshrao9993/laptop-specification-dataset | 984 laptop entries. Also: `sohaibdevv/modern-laptop-prices-and-specifications` (30 modern laptops, 2025-2026). | Free static datasets. Not auto-updating. | N/A |
| **SidHacksCommunity/Laptop-Specification-api** | https://github.com/SidHacksCommunity/Laptop-Specification-api | Community-maintained laptop dataset on GitHub. | Free, open source. Limited coverage. | None |

**Recommendation for Laptops**: This is the weakest category for free sources. The best strategy is:
1. Use **MobileAPI.dev** (covers laptops) for structured data within the 50 req/month free tier.
2. Build a **custom NotebookCheck scraper** using Python (BeautifulSoup + requests) for comprehensive laptop data. NotebookCheck has the deepest laptop spec database.
3. Supplement with **TechSpecs API** free trial for initial data seeding, but do NOT rely on it long-term due to caching restrictions.

