## 4. FREE PRODUCT IMAGE SOURCES

| Source | URL | What It Offers | Free Tier | API Key |
|--------|-----|---------------|-----------|---------|
| **Brandfetch Logo API** | https://brandfetch.com/developers/logo-api | Access to hundreds of millions of brand logos. Always up-to-date. | Logo API is completely free (fair use limits). Brand API has 100 free requests. | Required (free signup for client ID) |
| **MobileAPI.dev Images** | https://mobileapi.dev/ | Multiple product images per device served as base64. Thumbnails available. | Included in 50 free requests/month | Required (free) |
| **Wikimedia Commons API** | https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/API:Images | Millions of freely licensed images including product photos. API access to search and retrieve. | Completely free. CC/public domain licenses. | Not required |
| **GSMArena (via scrapers)** | N/A | Phone product images available through the self-hosted GSMArena scrapers. | Unlimited (self-hosted) | None |
| **Unsplash API** | https://unsplash.com/developers | High-quality photos, free for commercial and non-commercial use. | 50 requests/hour (Production), free | Required (free) |

**Recommendation**: Use **GSMArena scraper images** for phones (already included in scraped data), **Brandfetch Logo API** for brand logos, and **Wikimedia Commons** for supplementary product photos. For car images, the GitHub datasets and NHTSA do not include images -- you would need to scrape from manufacturer sites or use Wikimedia Commons.

