## 6. FREE AI / REVIEW GENERATION

### 6.1 Free Cloud LLM APIs

| Source | URL | What It Offers | Free Tier Limits | API Key |
|--------|-----|---------------|-----------------|---------|
| **Google Gemini API** | https://ai.google.dev/ | Gemini 2.5 Pro, Flash, Flash Lite models. Text generation, summarization. | Free tier: ~5 requests/minute, ~50 requests/day (varies by model). Sufficient for batch processing ~50 product reviews/day. | Required (free) |
| **Groq Cloud** | https://groq.com/ | Ultra-fast inference. Llama 3.3, Llama 4 Scout, Mixtral, Gemma. | ~30 requests/minute, ~14,400 requests/day. Per-model token limits (~12K tokens/min). Very generous. | Required (free) |
| **Cerebras** | https://cerebras.ai/ | Fast inference for Llama models. | Free tier available | Required (free) |
| **NVIDIA NIM** | https://build.nvidia.com/ | Various open models hosted by NVIDIA. | Free tier, no credit card | Required (free) |
| **OpenRouter** | https://openrouter.ai/ | Aggregator for many LLM providers. Some free models available. | Free models available (rate limited) | Required (free) |

### 6.2 Self-Hosted LLM Solutions (Truly Free, Unlimited)

| Source | URL | What It Offers |
|--------|-----|---------------|
| **Ollama** | https://ollama.com/ | Run Llama 3, Mistral, Gemma, Phi-3, and many other open-source models locally. Completely free, unlimited. |
| **LM Studio** | https://lmstudio.ai/ | Desktop app for running local LLMs. GUI-based, easy model management. Includes local API server. |
| **llama.cpp** | https://github.com/ggerganov/llama.cpp | Lightweight C++ inference. Can run on CPU. Good for CI/CD pipelines. |
| **vLLM** | https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm | High-throughput, production-grade inference server. |

**Recommendation for AI Reviews**:
- **Best balance**: Use **Groq Cloud** free tier (~14,400 req/day is more than enough for generating reviews for hundreds of products daily). Llama 3.3 70B on Groq produces high-quality product reviews.
- **Truly unlimited**: Self-host **Ollama** with Llama 3 8B or Mistral 7B. Can run on any machine with 8GB+ RAM. Expose a local API endpoint your pipeline calls.
- **For GitHub Actions CI**: Use Gemini or Groq free cloud APIs since self-hosting isn't practical in ephemeral CI runners.

