## 7. FREE AUTOMATION TOOLS

| Source | URL | What It Offers | Free Tier | Notes |
|--------|-----|---------------|-----------|-------|
| **GitHub Actions** (already in use) | https://github.com/features/actions | Cron-triggered workflows. 2,000 free minutes/month on public repos. | Free for public repos. 2,000 min/month for private. | Already your primary automation. |
| **n8n (self-hosted)** | https://n8n.io/ | Open-source workflow automation. Visual editor. 400+ integrations. Webhook triggers, cron. | Completely free when self-hosted. Cloud version has paid tiers. | Can run on Google Cloud free tier (e2-micro instance). |
| **Python Scraping Libraries** | N/A | BeautifulSoup4, Scrapy, Selenium, Playwright, httpx, requests-html. | All completely free, open source. | Already using Python pipeline (`tools/run_all.py`). |
| **cron-job.org** | https://cron-job.org/ | Free online cron service to trigger webhooks on schedule. | Free (up to 60 jobs, 5-min minimum interval). | Good for triggering GitHub Actions externally. |
| **Make.com** | https://www.make.com/ | Visual workflow automation. | Free: 1,000 operations/month. Very limited. | Too restrictive for daily data pipelines. |

**Python Scraping Library Recommendations** (ranked by suitability for your use case):

1. **Scrapy** -- Best for large-scale, structured scraping. Async, fast, extensible. Has built-in pipeline support for data export.
2. **BeautifulSoup4 + httpx** -- Best for simple page-by-page extraction. Easy to integrate into existing `run_all.py`.
3. **Playwright** -- Best for JavaScript-heavy sites that require browser rendering (some modern product pages).
4. **requests-html** -- Lightweight alternative combining requests + parsing + JS rendering.

