## 8. NEW PRODUCT DETECTION

| Source | URL | What It Offers | How to Use |
|--------|-----|---------------|-----------|
| **GSMArena RSS Feeds** | https://rss.app/rss-feed/gsmarena-com-rss-feed | Auto-updating RSS feed of GSMArena articles/news (updates every 15 min). | Parse RSS XML with Python `feedparser` library. Extract new phone announcements. |
| **GSMArena Latest Endpoint** | Via self-hosted scraper: `GET /latest` | Returns latest added devices directly from GSMArena. | Already available in RevengerNick/mobile-specs-api. |
| **Feedspot Smartphone RSS Feeds** | https://rss.feedspot.com/smartphone_rss_feeds/ | Curated list of top 35 smartphone RSS feeds from major tech sites. | Subscribe to multiple feeds for cross-source detection. |
| **Gadgets360** | https://www.gadgets360.com/mobiles/news | Latest mobile news with RSS support. | Parse RSS for new launch announcements. |
| **Android Headlines** | https://www.androidheadlines.com/ | Android phone news. RSS available. | RSS parsing. |
| **Telegram Channels** | e.g., `MishaalAndroidNews` | Real-time Android leak/launch news. | Can be scraped via Telegram API (free). |
| **TechCrunch / The Verge / Engadget** | Various | Major tech news outlets with RSS feeds. | Parse for product launch keywords. |
| **MobileAPI.dev Browse by Year** | https://mobileapi.dev/ | Endpoints to list devices by launch year. New devices added within 2-6 hours of announcement. | Poll the API for new entries (but limited to 50 req/month on free tier). |

**Recommended New Product Detection Pipeline**:
1. Set up a Python script using `feedparser` to poll GSMArena RSS + 5-10 tech news RSS feeds every few hours.
2. Cross-reference discovered product names against your existing `data.js` database.
3. For new products, trigger the full scraping pipeline to fetch specs from GSMArena via the self-hosted API.
4. Optionally use Groq/Gemini free API to auto-generate initial reviews for newly detected products.

